	<p>At Rembolt Ludtke LLP, our litigation practice encompasses virtually every area of civil litigation. Though much of it focuses on business-related matters, we also handle numerous personal cases such as divorce, personal injury, wrongful death, and adoption.<span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>
<h2>Diversity of Practice Areas</h2>
<p>The diversity of practice areas in the Firm provides the litigators with expert advice in-house, enabling them to provide effective representation in a variety of matters. Further, we make extensive use of paralegals and law clerks to help minimize the cost to clients.<span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>
<p>Our attorneys appear in Nebraska state and federal courts (including the Eighth Circuit Court of Appeals) on both the trial and appellate level. We also represent clients in administrative proceedings before local, state, and federal governmental agencies.<span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>
<h2>Practical, Results-Oriented Approach</h2>
<p>Our ultimate goal is to provide practical and results-oriented legal services. We recognize that a trial in a court of law may be the least favorable outcome for all parties involved. That is why we work diligently to resolve matters in a fair and cost-effective manner and avoid the uncertainties and expense involved in a trial. We accomplish this through a combination of thorough case preparation, a realistic analysis of the law and the facts, and the use of various means of alternative dispute resolution.</p>
